etymologies: late 16th century. From ancient Greek Πυλαγόρας delegate sent to the Amphictyonic Council from Πύλαι, the name of the Thermopylae (the older place of assembly of the Pythian Amphictyony) + ἀγορά

definitions: Chiefly in plural. Either of the two deputies sent by each constituent State to the Amphictyonic Council.
